Name: Watery Dash
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Charge|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. Additionally while wielding this weapon you gain a swimming speed equal to twice your walking speed, but you can only swim in a straight line and you get advantage on the attack while underwater.

Name: Grasping Grass
Description: You get the benefits of the {@optfeature Topple|ingensorenth} Orenth Trait. Additionally, whenever a creature fails the saving throw you may choose to restrain them too as vines sprout from the ground. This effect lasts until the end of your next turn. You may do so a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Beat him up boys
Description: You get the benefits of the {@optfeature Vex|ingensorenth} Orenth Trait. Additionally, whenever you successfully hit a creature to gain advantage you may choose to give any ally advantage on attack rolls against them until the start of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Acidic Vex
Description: You get the benefits of the {@optfeature Vex|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. Whenever you hit a creature you may forgo the advantage from vex and instead deal an additional 2d4 acid damage when you hit.

Name: Poisonous Graze
Description: You get the benefits of the {@optfeature Graze|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. The damage you deal with graze is increased by 1d8 poison damage.

Name: Aura of Cold
Description: As a bonus action you can activate your aura. While your aura is active, any creature that starts its turn within 5 feet of you becomes slowed. They remain slowed until they end a turn further than 5 feet away from you. It remains as long as you keep concentrating on it.

Name: Expert Moonstone Steps
Description: Youâ€™ve become an expert at stepping in and out of reality. When you use your bonus action for Moonstone Steps you gain a teleporting speed equal to your walking speed.

Name: Psionic Topple
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Topple|ingensorenth} Orenth trait, however, the target must succeed on an Intelligence saving throw instead.

Name: Illusory Graze
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Graze|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. However, whenever you miss a creature they take psychic damage equal to the ability modifier you used for the attack roll plus your Intelligence modifier instead.

Name: Telekinetic Weapon
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Nick|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. Additionally, the weapon that has Nick applied to it, no longer requires a free hand to wield.

Name: Big Skin
Description: Your skin hardens like Big, giving you resistance to bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage.

Name: Acquired Immunity
Description: When you take damage you may reduce the damage by 1. The damage reduction increases by 1 every subsequent time you take damage. The damage reduction returns to 1 when you don't take damage for an entire round.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Topple
Description: Whenever a creature fails the saving throw against your Topple Orenth Trait, their speed is reduced to 0 until the end of your next turn.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Flex
Description: Whenever you hit with the weapon that your Flex Orenth trait applies to, you may roll the damage die twice.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Sap
Description: You get the benefits of the Sap Orenth trait, but the creature gains disadvantage on all attacks before the start of your next turn.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Slow
Description: Whenever you hit a creature their speed is reduced to 0 until the start of your next turn.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Deflective Weapons
Description: The amount of dice you roll when you use your Deflective Weapons Orenth trait doubles. Additionally the armour class increase lasts until the start of your next turn.

Name: Distracting Mockery
Description: Whenever a creature uses a reaction within 30 feet of you, you may use your reaction to force them to make a Wisdom saving throw (DC = 8+ your prof. bonus + your Charisma modifier). On a failure they take 1d4 psychic damage and lose their reaction.

Name: Inspired Vex
Description: You gain the benefits of the {@optfeature Vex|ingensorenth} Orenth trait. Additionally, whenever you hit a creature you may also choose to give an ally advantage on their next attack they make against the creature before the start of your next turn.

Name: Living Legend
Description: Stories have been spread about your great deeds and the people's belief in you bolsters you. You may use your Charisma modifier instead of your Constitution for calculating your hp.

Name: Formidable Recovery
Description: Choose a tier 1 Orenth trait that gives you a first level spellslot back. You may instead get a fourth level spellslot back. The orenth type of this trait is the same as the tier 1 trait you choose.  You cannot choose the same tier 1 trait in this way twice.

Name: Multitasking
Description: Choose a spell of a level equal to your proficiency bonus divided by 3 (rounded down). Whenever you cast this spell it doesn't require concentration.

Name: Surviving Summoner
Description: Choose a spell that summons a creature. Whenever the creature you summoned is reduced to zero hit points it doesn't disappear, it instead falls unconscious and gets to make death saving throws. Only when it fails all death saves does it dissapear.

Name: Active Concentration
Description: Choose a spell that requires concentration. Instead of concentration on the spell you may instead use a bonus action on each of your turns the spell is active to keep the spell up. You immediately start concentrating on the spell when you don't use your bonus action on a turn for this purpose. You may still only have one concentration spell active at a time.

Name: Winged Kobold
Description: You gain a flying speed equal to half your walking speed. You cannot fly while wearing medium or heavy armour.

Name: Metallic Kobold Summoner
Description: After you finish a long rest a number of Kobolds equal to your proficiency bonus appears. They are always charmed by you. The kobold can cast Healing Word once per long rest and take the help action as a bonus action.

Name: Chromatic Kobold Summoner
Description: After you finish a long rest a number of Kobolds equal to your proficiency bonus appears. They are always charmed by you. Their Strength, Dexterity and Constitution score increase by 4.

Name: Gem Kobold Summoner
Description: After you finish a long rest a number of Kobolds equal to your proficiency bonus appears. They are always charmed by you. They can cast one cantrip of your choice, using their Intelligence as their spellcasting ability

Name: Luckiest
Description: When you roll a 2 on an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, you can reroll the die and must use the new roll.

Name: Precious Rings
Description: You may attune to one additional magic item. This magic item must be a ring.

Name: Fey Bargain: Flight
Description: You gain a flying speed equal to your walking speed. However, whenever you end your turn more than 15 feet in the air you must make a Wisdom saving throw (DC=10+your proficiency bonus). On a failure you become frightened, making you unable to fly any higher until the condition ends. The condition ends when you land.

Name: Blessed Breath
Description:
Additional Breath Weapon* You gain an additional use of your breath weapon. 
Blessed Breath* Whenever you use your breath weapon you may choose any creature in the area that doesn't take damage. This creature can add 1d4 to attack rolls and saving throws for a number of rounds equal to your charisma modifier.

Name: Giant Spell
Description: Choose a spell with a radius or cube area of effect. Whenever you cast this spell its size is doubled.

Name: Unlocked Memories
Description: Once per short rest you may enter a short trance as an action, recalling lost and forgotten memories. For the next minute your proficiency bonus increases by 2, but you cannot remember anything you do during this minute.

Name: Inspiring Presence
Description: At the start of each of your turns you gain a d4 Presence die. You may add this die to any dice roll made within 60 feet of you as a reaction.

Name: Greatwyrm Dragon Breath
Description: Whenever you roll for initiative and you have no more Breath Weapons remaining, you regain one use of it. Whenever you start your turn with no Breath Weapons remanining you may roll 1d6. If you roll a 5 or a 6 you regain a use of your breath weapon.

Name: Fire Aura
Description: A flaming aura forms in a 15 foot emanation around you. Whenever you deal fire damage to a creature in this emanation they take additional damage equal to your Wisdom modifier.

Name: Lighting Aura
Description: Whenever any creature of your choice makes a Dexterity, Strength or Constitution saving throw within 15 feet of you, they must subtract 1d4 from the roll. If they still succeed they take lightning damage equal to your Wisdom modifier.

Name: Vine Aura
Description: As a bonus action you may summon a vine that grapples a creature within 15 feet of you.The DC for the saving throw and any escape attempts equals 8 plus your Wisdom modifier and Proficiency Bonus. This grapple is possible only if the target is no more than one size larger than you. Once the creature escapes the vine shrivels away.

Name: Water Aura
Description: As a bonus action you may cast your acid splash cantrip as a 15 foot emanation.

Name: Wind Aura
Description: As a bonus action you may push any creature of your choice within 15 feet of you, 15 feet away if they fail a strength saving throw (DC=8+your proficiency bonus+your Wisdom modifier). Additionally may fly up to 15 feet after using this bonus action.

Name: Spore Aura
Description: Whenever any creature of your choice makes a Intelligence, Wisdom or Charisma saving throw within 15 feet of you, they must subtract 1d4 from the roll. If they still succeed they take psychic damage equal to your Wisdom modifier.

Name: Earth Shift
Description: At the start of your turn you may immediately swap places with any creature within 15 feet of you, as long as the space you are in fits the other creature.

Name: Where the fuck did you find that
Prerequisite: {@optfeature It's the same size as you|otherorenth}
Description: The CR of the creature you can find increases to 3.

Name: Geckofolk
Description: You gain a climbing speed equal to your walking speed. Additionally you may move on vertical surfaces and ceilings while keeping your hands fee.

Name: Large infernal wings
Description: You gain a 30 foot flying speed. You cannot fly while wearing medium or heavy armour.

Name: Crossed
Description: You learn to make nice wooden crosses. Whenever you grapple someone they start suffocating.
